\f0\fs24 \cf0 An unleveling of the hips is generally from one of two problems.  Either one leg is shorter than the other or there is a "torquing" of the pelvis due to a muscle imbalance generally involving the psoas muscles.  If the cause is an actual short leg then if severe enough it needs to be corrected for with either a heel lift in one side or a building up of the sole of the shoe on that side.  If is due to a muscular imbalance and torquing of the pelvis, generally stretching ot the psoas muscles and abdominal strengthening are indicated.}